WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.270 --> 00:00:02.770
DANIEL ALEGRE: Buongiorno.

00:00:02.770 --> 00:00:04.400
Hello, good morning.

00:00:04.400 --> 00:00:05.450
I'm Daniel Alegre.

00:00:05.450 --> 00:00:08.150
I'm responsible for Google's
global partnerships.

00:00:08.150 --> 00:00:10.470
And it's just an
incredible morning.

00:00:10.470 --> 00:00:12.220
It's great to see so
many people out here.

00:00:12.220 --> 00:00:14.040
There are a few seats
up here in the front.

00:00:14.040 --> 00:00:16.830
Please come up, for
those who are standing.

00:00:16.830 --> 00:00:17.440
Yes, please.

00:00:17.440 --> 00:00:18.445
Please come up.

00:00:18.445 --> 00:00:21.355
[LAUGHTER]

00:00:28.145 --> 00:00:28.760
Oh, no, no.

00:00:32.416 --> 00:00:35.859
That's for Veronica.

00:00:35.859 --> 00:00:36.805
No, no.

00:00:41.540 --> 00:00:42.650
OK.

00:00:42.650 --> 00:00:43.500
Thank you.

00:00:43.500 --> 00:00:44.360
Great excitement.

00:00:44.360 --> 00:00:47.782
Obviously, you're
not here to see me.

00:00:47.782 --> 00:00:49.160
That's too bad.

00:00:49.160 --> 00:00:50.840
Andrea Bocelli.

00:00:50.840 --> 00:00:53.450
What can be said about
this inspirational artist

00:00:53.450 --> 00:00:55.140
and human being?

00:00:55.140 --> 00:00:56.140
I'll give it a shot.

00:00:56.140 --> 00:01:00.530
Maestro Bocelli has recorded
15 solo studio albums, three

00:01:00.530 --> 00:01:03.750
greatest hits albums,
and nine complete operas,

00:01:03.750 --> 00:01:07.250
selling over 80 million
records worldwide.

00:01:07.250 --> 00:01:12.910
In 1998, he was named one
of People Magazine's 50

00:01:12.910 --> 00:01:14.650
most beautiful people.

00:01:14.650 --> 00:01:17.370
In 1999, he was nominated
for the Best New Artist

00:01:17.370 --> 00:01:18.970
at the Grammy Awards.

00:01:18.970 --> 00:01:21.500
The Prayer, his duet
with Celine Dion,

00:01:21.500 --> 00:01:23.780
won the Golden Globe
for best original song

00:01:23.780 --> 00:01:27.330
and was nominated for an Academy
Award in the same category.

00:01:27.330 --> 00:01:31.080
With the release of his
classical album, Sacred Arias,

00:01:31.080 --> 00:01:33.860
Bocelli captured a listing
in the Guinness Book

00:01:33.860 --> 00:01:35.900
of World Records as
he simultaneously

00:01:35.900 --> 00:01:40.500
had the top three positions on
the US Classical Album Charts.

00:01:40.500 --> 00:01:41.770
Never done before.

00:01:41.770 --> 00:01:44.350
Seven of his albums have
since reached top 10

00:01:44.350 --> 00:01:46.350
in the Billboard 200.

00:01:46.350 --> 00:01:48.690
With five million
units sold worldwide,

00:01:48.690 --> 00:01:51.880
Sacred Arias became the
biggest-selling classical album

00:01:51.880 --> 00:01:54.620
by a solo artist of all time.

00:01:54.620 --> 00:01:57.190
And now, with over 20 million
copies sold worldwide,

00:01:57.190 --> 00:02:01.190
his 1997 album, Romanza,
became the bestselling album

00:02:01.190 --> 00:02:06.290
by any Italian artist
in his genre in history.

00:02:06.290 --> 00:02:08.870
Maestro Bocelli was
made grand officer

00:02:08.870 --> 00:02:12.350
of the Order of the Merit of
the Italian Republic in 2006.

00:02:12.350 --> 00:02:14.190
And he was also honored
with the Hollywood

00:02:14.190 --> 00:02:17.890
Walk of Fame for his
contribution to live theater.

00:02:17.890 --> 00:02:19.400
Maestro Bocelli
recently released

00:02:19.400 --> 00:02:22.140
Cinema, his 15th
studio album, featuring

00:02:22.140 --> 00:02:25.190
renditions of classical
film soundtracks and scores.

00:02:25.190 --> 00:02:27.600
And in 2011, something that
is very important to him

00:02:27.600 --> 00:02:29.440
and very personal,
Maestro Bocelli

00:02:29.440 --> 00:02:32.200
founded the Andrea
Bocelli Foundation,

00:02:32.200 --> 00:02:35.360
whose goal is to enable
the less fortunate or weak

00:02:35.360 --> 00:02:38.055
to have the possibly to have
a better future of beauty

00:02:38.055 --> 00:02:38.805
and opportunities.

00:02:43.330 --> 00:02:46.840
It is incredible to have
such an individual here

00:02:46.840 --> 00:02:52.630
and an internationally-renowned
artist, dedicated family man,

00:02:52.630 --> 00:02:57.832
and philanthropist with a true
purpose to change the world.

00:02:57.832 --> 00:02:59.540
Maestro Bocelli will
be accompanied today

00:02:59.540 --> 00:03:03.790
by pianist Eugene Kohn, who
will be joining us up here.

00:03:03.790 --> 00:03:07.432
And if we give them a very,
very, very warm welcome,

00:03:07.432 --> 00:03:09.140
maybe we'll also be
able to convince them

00:03:09.140 --> 00:03:12.340
to sing a song or two for us.

00:03:12.340 --> 00:03:13.840
Ladies and gentlemen,
please join me

00:03:13.840 --> 00:03:16.635
in giving Andrea Bocelli
a warm welcome to Google.

00:03:16.635 --> 00:03:20.912
[APPLAUSE]

00:03:34.649 --> 00:03:35.732
ANDREA BOCELLI: Thank you.

00:03:42.180 --> 00:03:44.210
Thank you very much.

00:03:44.210 --> 00:03:47.490
Thank you for this invitation.

00:03:47.490 --> 00:03:54.180
All my friends will be very
jealous because honestly,

00:03:54.180 --> 00:03:57.620
me too, I was very
curious to be here.

00:03:57.620 --> 00:04:00.870
And thank you also
for the presentation.

00:04:00.870 --> 00:04:08.830
Also, I think that if somebody
here is able to use Google,

00:04:08.830 --> 00:04:12.280
I think it's possible to
find every kind of news

00:04:12.280 --> 00:04:16.220
about me online.

00:04:16.220 --> 00:04:19.594
So thank you very much
for this opportunity.

00:04:23.810 --> 00:04:27.620
I tell you, sadly, that
I prefer to speak Italian

00:04:27.620 --> 00:04:29.100
because my English is horrible.

00:04:29.100 --> 00:04:37.270
So I want to be clear to
answer to your questions.

00:04:37.270 --> 00:04:42.430
But I know I have a
very nice interpreter.

00:04:42.430 --> 00:04:48.600
So I'll give you
the words and I will

00:04:48.600 --> 00:04:51.205
answer to every kind of
question you want to pose me.

00:04:51.205 --> 00:04:52.080
DANIEL ALEGRE: Great.

00:04:52.080 --> 00:04:55.070
Well, first, thank
you and welcome.

00:04:55.070 --> 00:04:55.820
Welcome to Google.

00:04:55.820 --> 00:04:57.970
And I'd say probably
everyone here

00:04:57.970 --> 00:05:00.130
in the audience has
friends who are saying

00:05:00.130 --> 00:05:03.890
they are so jealous that we get
to see-- experience-- Maestro

00:05:03.890 --> 00:05:06.527
Bocelli here live, including my
mother, my sister, my brother,

00:05:06.527 --> 00:05:07.110
and my father.

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:14.030
You just flew in from Seattle.

00:05:14.030 --> 00:05:15.600
I know I also
appreciate you being

00:05:15.600 --> 00:05:17.220
here at such an early hour.

00:05:17.220 --> 00:05:19.310
Because I think you landed
from Seattle around 2,

00:05:19.310 --> 00:05:21.600
3 o'clock in the morning.

00:05:21.600 --> 00:05:23.290
How are you feeling
this morning?

00:05:23.290 --> 00:05:25.580
ANDREA BOCELLI: I flew
by Italy yesterday.

00:05:25.580 --> 00:05:28.940
Then I had a concert
yesterday evening.

00:05:28.940 --> 00:05:35.787
And now I'm here, so it means
that I'm still strong enough.

00:05:35.787 --> 00:05:37.220
DANIEL ALEGRE: OK, good.

00:05:37.220 --> 00:05:41.970
Well, you were supposed to
perform on Saturday at San Jose

00:05:41.970 --> 00:05:44.930
SAP Arena, and the
concert was moved

00:05:44.930 --> 00:05:49.780
to Friday because of the
success of the San Jose Sharks.

00:05:49.780 --> 00:05:50.880
So for anyone who is--

00:05:50.880 --> 00:05:52.020
[APPLAUSE]

00:05:52.020 --> 00:05:57.300
So I guess we have some
San Jose Sharks fans here.

00:05:57.300 --> 00:06:01.760
But you perform in some of the
largest, most beautiful venues

00:06:01.760 --> 00:06:05.210
in the world, whether it's
Carnegie Hall, the Wiener

00:06:05.210 --> 00:06:09.510
Staatsoper, the
Metropolitan Opera House.

00:06:09.510 --> 00:06:11.830
And you travel everywhere
around the world,

00:06:11.830 --> 00:06:17.150
meet celebrities, meet
all the different popes.

00:06:17.150 --> 00:06:19.480
I guess the question is,
how do you stay grounded?

00:06:19.480 --> 00:06:21.620
You know, what is normal
for Andrea Bocelli?

00:06:21.620 --> 00:06:26.504
INTERPRETER: [SPEAKING ITALIAN]

00:06:28.490 --> 00:06:31.330
ANDREA BOCELLI:
[SPEAKING  ITALIAN]

