00:18:53.040 --> 00:18:56.120
is a very special message.

00:18:59.380 --> 00:19:02.100
DANIEL ALEGRE: And
it also made you

00:19:02.100 --> 00:19:06.090
as a well-known household name.

00:19:06.090 --> 00:19:10.720
And it's been recorded in
Portuguese, Spanish, French,

00:19:10.720 --> 00:19:13.000
multiple languages.

00:19:13.000 --> 00:19:16.630
Do you still like performing
it or does it become a burden

00:19:16.630 --> 00:19:17.620
after so many times?

00:19:17.620 --> 00:19:21.200
ANDREA BOCELLI:
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

00:19:21.720 --> 00:19:23.460
INTERPRETER: What
I like to do is

00:19:23.460 --> 00:19:27.240
to see how much
people like my songs.

00:19:27.240 --> 00:19:29.150
DANIEL ALEGRE: That's great.

00:19:29.150 --> 00:19:32.570
And I think that leads me to
an obvious question for someone

00:19:32.570 --> 00:19:37.510
who has such a passion
for music and for art.

00:19:37.510 --> 00:19:41.190
How does it feel for you
that your passion is also

00:19:41.190 --> 00:19:43.260
a profession?

00:19:43.260 --> 00:19:46.840
The commercial expectations
